<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
Head and body dark brown (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
), fore wing basally with brown infuscation (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Antenna (in female) with 4 anelli (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
). Clava elongate, about 6 times as long as broad and 1.5 times as long as scape length (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Fore wing 2.9 times as long as broad, anteriorly with 4 setae, posterior margin of hind wing disc slightly rounded.
</paragraph>
