<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Description (female holotype).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Colour.</emphasis>
Head dark brown (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
), legs brown with tarsi pale yellow (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
), antenna brown with radicle and basal 3 funicle antennomeres pale yellow (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Fore wing basally with brown infuscation, and a darker patch behind distal part of submarginal vein and proximal part of marginal vein, and longitudinal dark patch along basal part of hind margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Morphology.</emphasis>
Head 1.69 times as broad as frontovertex width (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
), frontovertex width subequal to length of clava, distance from mouth margin to facial ridge 0.66. Antenna with 4 anelli, increasing in size towards apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
), clava about 6 times as long as broad and 1.5 times as long as scape length, pedicel about 0.5 times as long as scape (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
). Midlobe of mesoscutum with 11 setae in posterior half, scutellum with 8 setae along posterior margin. Fore wing 2.9 times as long as broad (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
), longest setae of marginal fringe 0.38 times as long as width of disc, seta M1 absent, M2b present (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Hind margin of hind wing disc slightly rounded and nearly parallel to anterior margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
). Mesofemur ventrally with 3 long spines (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Midtibial spur 0.7 times as long as corresponding basitarsus (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chartocerus sumatrensis Schmidt &amp; Polaszek, sp. nov., female holotype A body in dorsal view B head in frontal view C middle leg D apex of middle femur E fore wing F hind wing G antenna H pedicel and flagellum base." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362573" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.897.38148.figure4">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
), the latter 0.53 times as long as midtibia. Ovipositor 2.9 times as long as midtibia and 2.0 times as long as hind tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="host">
